---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Justin Doone"
  description="15+ years of marketing, mostly for financial services firms. Financial communications and IR in Hong Kong, real estate PE/AM at Greybrook and Clifton Blake in Toronto, now ETFs at Evolve."
>
  <!-- HERO (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative pt-24 md:pt-36 pb-12 md:pb-16">
    <div class="hero-orb hero-orb-a" style="top: -10%; right: -15%;"></div>
    <div
      class="hero-orb hero-orb-b"
      style="bottom: -25%; left: 0%; opacity: 0.25; background: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-accent-cool), transparent 60%);"
    ></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <img
        src="/images/profile.jpg"
        alt="Justin Doone"
        width="200"
        height="200"
        class="hero-line w-36 h-36 md:w-44 md:h-44 rounded-full object-cover mb-10 ring-1 ring-on-dark-mute"
        data-line="0"
      />
      <p class="hero-line eyebrow mb-8" data-line="0">About</p>
      <h1
        class="hero-line heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-10 leading-[0.95]"
        data-line="1"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        15+ years of marketing, mostly for <em style="color: var(--color-accent); font-style: italic;">financial services</em> firms.
      </h1>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6"
        data-line="2"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        Started in Hong Kong: financial communications at agencies, in-house investor relations at a publicly listed company, hospitality marketing at a boutique hotel. Moved to Toronto for real estate PE/AM at Greybrook and Clifton Blake. Currently at Evolve, running digital marketing for a 41-fund ETF lineup.
      </p>
      <p
        class="hero-line text-lg leading-relaxed"
        data-line="3"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        Mostly lean teams. More of the marketing function on me than the title would suggest. More tooling I've built because off-the-shelf didn't fit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK (dark, continued) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-16 md:py-20" data-reveal>
    <div
      class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 rule-top pt-16"
    >
      <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
      <div
        class="space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-lg"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark-soft);"
      >
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
          I do the analytics part myself. Pulling the data, building the dashboards I need, the meeting where someone argues their channel deserves more credit. On bigger teams that's a separate role. The teams I've been on have always had me doing both, which keeps the strategy from drifting from what the data actually shows.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
          A lot of what I do these days is build small AI-assisted tools for the team. Reporting that consolidates the ad platforms into one view, competitive intel on what other firms are running in market, end-of-month update tools that automate the recurring chores. Most of the small teams I've worked on don't have off-the-shelf options that fit, and AI assist lets me build the missing pieces in days.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
          Most of my work has been in financial services and similar regulated industries. You learn to write copy with legal in mind from the first draft. Skipping that step usually means launching a quarter late after compliance kicks it back.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-24 md:py-32" data-reveal>
    <div class="hero-orb" style="top: 0%; right: -10%; opacity: 0.3;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
      <h2
        class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8"
        style="color: var(--color-on-dark);"
      >
        Tell me what you're trying to ship.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="mailto:justindoone@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent-warm transition-colors"
      >
        justindoone@gmail.com
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
